A world renowned forensic pathologist has recreated the last hours of Michael Hutchence's infamous death with the help of the original coroner. 

Dr Richard Shepherd has sifted through the autopsy and toxicology reports related to the famous INXS rocker's death as part of a television series set to air  in Australia on Channel 7 next week.

The 45-minute episode, titled Autopsy: The Last Hours of Michael Hutchence, pieces together the events and considers the state of mind Hutchence was in before he took his own life at the Carlton Ritz Hotel in November 1997. 

