Dr Shepherd said the toxicology report showed there was a mixture of cocaine, alcohol and the anti-depressant Prozac in his blood when he died.

The episode revealed that Hutchence had started taking the prescription anti-depressant after suffering a blow to head in a fight with a taxi driver in 1993.

The incident, which occurred while he was dating girlfriend at the time Helena Christensen, led him to lose all sense of smell and taste.

Dr Shepherd said his use of Prozac was erratic and led to increased use of other drugs in the years prior to his death.

