'There are so many twists and turns in the medical evidence, putting them all in the correct order and reaching a final conclusion can be very difficult,' Dr Shepherd said.

His death was reported by the NSW Coroner to be the result of suicide after he was found hanging on the back of his hotel door with a belt around his neck.

But his girlfriend Paula Yates publicly insisted Hutchence had died accidentally during a sex game gone wrong - a fact examined by Dr Shepherd in his episode.

